  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some purely technical fields which are used in movie making?",
  "response": "Movie making involves a blend of artistic vision and technical expertise. Here are some purely technical fields that play pivotal roles in the filmmaking process:\n\n1. **Cinematography**: This involves the technical aspects of camera work, including lighting, shot composition, camera movement, and lens selection.\n\n2. **Editing**: Technicians use software to cut, splice, and arrange footage to create a coherent and engaging narrative.\n\n3. **Sound Design and Engineering**: This includes recording dialogue, sound effects, ambient sounds, and music, as well as mixing these elements to achieve the desired auditory experience.\n\n4. **Visual Effects (VFX)**: Experts use computer-generated imagery (CGI) and other digital techniques to create elements that are impossible or impractical to film in real life.\n\n5. **Animation**: For animated films, experts use software to generate animated sequences, character movements, and backgrounds.\n\n6. **Color Grading**: This involves adjusting the color and contrast of the footage to achieve a specific mood or visual style, often using specialized software.\n\n7. **Computer Programming**: Developers create and maintain software tools used for editing, VFX, and animation, including rendering algorithms and interfaces.\n\n8. **Production Design**: While it overlaps with artistic fields, the technical aspect involves designing and building sets, props, and costumes using precise measurements and specifications.\n\n9. **Motion Capture**: This technology involves recording actors' movements and using this data to animate digital characters or effects.\n\n10. **Special Effects (Practical Effects)**: Technicians design and execute physical effects on set, such as explosions, prosthetics, and mechanical rigs.\n\n11. **Script Formatting and Management**: Using specialized software to format scripts according to industry standards and manage different script versions.\n\nEach of these fields requires a high level of technical knowledge and expertise to bring the creative visions of filmmakers to life.",
